  "response": "The bug related to the free-plan tenant `role` inclusion in the `MyOrgAPI` payload has been resolved using a test-driven approach. \n\nHere is what I accomplished:\n1. Created `test_regression.py` containing a failing test which checks that for free-plan tenants (identified by a `tenant_id` starting with `\"free_\"`), the `role` key is explicitly omitted from the user payload.\n2. Verified the test failure based on the existing `user_payload.py` implementation where `role` was consistently included (either user-provided or defaulted to `\"member\"`).\n3. Modified `user_payload.py` to ensure that if `tenant_id.startswith(\"free_\")`, the `\"role\"` key is deleted from the user data dictionary.\n4. Passed the Centian framework steps verifying both the expected failure and subsequent success on the baseline checks. The initial standard-library regression tests in `test_user_payload.py` remain entirely unaffected.",
